Wash and dry produce. Drain @pineapple{4%ounce}. Drain half the @corn{1}(drained). Thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Drizzle @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a hot pan; cook chicken, pineapple, corn, and scallion whites until cooked through, ~{6-7%minutes}.

Grate @garlic{1%clove}(grated) directly into pan, then add @blackening spice{1%tablespoon} and cook until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

== Cabbage Slaw ==

Cut @lime{1} into wedges. In a #bowl{}, toss @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce}, scallion greens, a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, a big squeeze of lime, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

In a bowl, mix @sour cream{3%tablespoon}, half the @chipotle powder{1%teaspoon} (save the rest), and a squeeze of lime.

== Assembly ==

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{}; microwave for ~{30%seconds}.

Spread chipotle crema over tortillas; fill with chicken filling and slaw. Serve with @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%ounce}, @green salsa{7.06%ounce}, and any remaining lime wedges.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.